import <https://raw.github.com/enriquepablo/terms.server/master/terms/server/app/ontology/tasks.trm>.

job-has-votes is unique, subj a job, many a number.

votes-job is abs-content-action, what a job, for a number.

has-voted-job is onwards, subj a person, what a job.

(is-protected votes-job, by manage-perm, for task-closed).
(is-protected votes-job, by edit-perm, for public).

(votes-job Person1, what Job1, for V1);
(job-has-votes Job1, many V2)
<-
condition &= V1 < 10

condition &= runtime.count('(has-voted-job %(Person1)s, what %(Job1)s)' % match) == 0

V3 = V2 + V1
->
(has-voted-job Person1, what Job1);
(job-has-votes Job1, many V3).

(wants Person1, do (votes-job Person1, for N1, what Job1));
(votes-job Person1, what Job1)
->
(votes-job Person1, what Job1, for N1).

(initialize Person1, obj Job1)
->
(job-has-votes Job1, many 0).
